#### Rooting hormone
###### Willow water recipe
- Can be derived organically from willow trees
	- ...which produce significant amounts of this hormone for themselves...
	- ...and can be extracted by boiling
		- ...and leaving leaves to soak overnight
		- ~10:1 water-willow ratio by volume
		- ...water used for this tends to resist mosquito larvae (anectodal)
	- Not as potent as synthetic varieties
	- Also produces [[Unsorted/Medicine#Aspirin\|Aspirin]] precursor
- Also acts as a fungicide

#### Auxins
- Responsible for plants' growth responses to gravity and light
- Direct effects
	- Disrupt cell matabolism
		- Can kill plants at high concentrations
		- Used as a weedkiller since monocots are more resistant
	- Depending on stage of growth:
		- Delays fruit ripening
		- Stimulates growth of flowers
		- Promotes femaleness (by producing ethylene)
- Mechanics
	- Moves away from lit leaves
		- inhibits growth
- Can be artificially produced
	- IAAs and NAAs
		- Sprayed on christmas trees to prevent budding and cone formation
		- Used to prevent potatoes from sprouting
	- 2,4-D, primary ingredient in agent orange
		- Kills dicots but not monocots
		- https://duckduckgo.com/?t=ffab&q=long+term+effects+of+agent+orange+in+vietnam+ecosystems
- Induces cell elongation in stems
- Creates 
- Stimulates cambium cell division
- Influences phloem-xylem differentiation
- Root initiation an ddevelopment
- Mediates respones of bending from gravity and light
	- Plants will not grow from upside-down cuttings
- Supresses growth of lateral buds
- Delays leaf senescence
- Can inhibit or promore leaf and fruit abcission
	- Separation from the plant
- Can induce fruit setting or growth in some plants

## Cytokinins
- Found in..
	- ...sites of active cell division
	- Root tips, stem tips, leaves
	- Meristomatic regions
	- Synthesized in the roots and transported to shoots through the xylem 
- Prompts Organogenesis
	- The process of developing a new organ
- Effects
	- Stimulates cell division
	- Stimulates morphogenesis
		- New organ development
	- Used by florists to increase shelf life by ~2 weeks
- Used in
	- Nearly all brassica are sprayed with cytokinins to increase shelf life
	- And in fruit trees


## Ethylene
- A gaseous hormone
- Only member of its class
- Produced by:
	- Ripening fruit
- Found in:
	- Can potentially be produced from HDPE? (question)
- Movement:
- Direct effects:
	- Promotes flower maleness
	- Stimulates:
		- Shoot an droot growth
		- Flower opening
		- Leaf and fruit abcission
	- In fruit
		- Less acidic
		- Sugar to starch
		- Less chlorophyll
		- Less pectin (softer)
		- Stronger fragrance
- Emergent effects:
	- Damages vegetables stored in the same container
- Applications:
	- Tomatoes are almost never picked ripe
		- Picked green, and gassed with ethylene to turn them red
		- Truly ripe ones bruise too easily
	- Has been used throughout history
		- As far back as [[Unsorted/The Egyptians\|Egypt]]

#### Gibberellins
Labelled: GA1,GA2,GA3
- GA3 is most common
	- AKA Gibberellic acid
- Produced by:
	- Plants in cold temperatures
- Found in:
- Movement:
- Direct effects:
	- Stimulates
		- Cell division and elongation
		- Bolting/flowering when days are long
		- Parthenogenic seedless fruit development
		- Breaking out of dormancy (Such as with seeds)
		- Maleness in deciduous flowers
- Emergent effects:
	- Prompts ripening
	- Increases size of ripened fruit
	- Increases sugar content
	- Longer nodes/internodes
- Applications:
	- Very frequently sprayed on grapes
		- Increases size
	- When applied to short-day plants
		- Plants become light green and stems split open from the fast growth
		- Can reach 10cm per day
		- When in female plants, creates male flowers that always produce female seeds when their pollen fertilizes a female flower

- Inhibited by Abscisic acid

# DIY Rooting Hormones
- Can be extracted from all willow species
	- Substances found in willow:
		- IBA and SA
		- IBA stimulates root growth (auxin)
	- Highly concentrated in the growing tips of willow branches
	- Processing
		- Materials needed
			- Get fresh willow branches, just the tips
		- Cut off growing tips
		- Soak them in water
			- It will leach out IBA
	- Growth
		- Don't grow in soil, only pots
			- Works for the first 5 years
			- Can re-propagate it from cuttings after that
		- They love to root into plumbing
